HEADWORD: extrovert
<hw>extrovert</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Psychol.)</fld> <def>A person who
is extroverted; a person who is marked by an interest in others or
concerned primarily with external reality. Contrasted with
<contr>introvert</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

